text: Günther Karl (born 4 January 1949) is a German rower who represented West Germany. He competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics in Mexico City with the men's coxless pair where they came twelfth. At the 1969 European Rowing Championships in Klagenfurt, he won bronze with the men's eight. ==References== Category:1949 births Category:Living people Category:German male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of West Germany Category:Rowers at the 1968 Summer Olympics Category:People from Passau Category:European Rowing Championships medalists
